{"questionId":"16151","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">Propene is an important starting material for many products. The following shows some compounds which can be made from propene, C<sub>3</sub>H<sub>6</sub>.</span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\"><br>Propene (C<sub>3</sub>H<sub>6</sub>) → C<sub>3</sub>H<sub>7</sub>Cl → C<sub>3</sub>H<sub>8</sub>O → C<sub>3</sub>H<sub>6</sub>O</span></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">Consider the conversion of propene to C<sub>3</sub>H<sub>7</sub>Cl.</span></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">State the type of reaction.</span></p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">«electrophilic» addition ✔</span></p>\n<p><em><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">NOTE:&nbsp;Do <strong>not</strong> accept “nucleophilic addition” or “free radical addition”.<br>Do <strong>not</strong> accept “halogenation”.</span></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"16151","referenceCode":"19N.2.hl.TZ0.3a(i)","subjectId":"45-dp-chemistry-last-assessment-2024","title":"State the type of reaction.","paper":"2","level":"HL","questionNumber":"a(i)","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Core","Core","Topic 10: Organic chemistry","10.2 Functional group chemistry","Core","Topic 10: Organic chemistry"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}